    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1864-01-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1864-01-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="27"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Dayton</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 401.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1864-01-21">
                            <hi rend="italic">January</hi> 21, 1864.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatches, from No. 451 to No. 454, both
                    inclusive, are duly received. No. 451 requests me to use my best endeavors to
                    procure evidence of the connexion of Bravay &amp; Co. with the insurgents. Mr.
                    Dudley, United States consul at Liverpool, had already informed me of the want
                    of this evidence, and I had made such inquiries as were in my power; and,
                    furthermore, had consulted with the English embassy here on this subject. I have
                    no doubt that such connexion between Bravay and the insurgents exists, but I
                    know not if evidence can be found to prove it.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WM. L. DAYTON.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, &amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
